-- Mouton 1945 Features With Latour at Christie’s Hong Kong
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-11-17T05:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-17/mouton-1945-features-with-latour-at-christie-s-hong-kong.html
Christie’s International Plc (BID)  holds
Hong Kong wine sales this week with historic Bordeaux including
first-growths Chateau Mouton-Rothschild 1945 and Chateau Latour
1961, as well as Chateau Cheval Blanc 1947 from Saint-Emilion.  A case of 1945 Mouton and a lot comprising a dozen bottles
of Cheval Blanc 1947 each carry an  estimate  of as much as HK$1.6
million ($206,400) for the sale on Nov. 23, while six magnums of
Latour 1961 are estimated at as much as HK$750,000, according to
the Christie’s online catalog.  A Burgundy-focused sale by Christie’s in Hong Kong on Nov.
24 features Romanee-Conti Grand Cru cases from recent vintages,
notably between 2004 and 2007, with 12 bottles of the 2005 wines
estimated at as much as HK$1.4 million.  Zachy’s is also holding a wine sale in  Hong Kong  today,
while Sotheby’s has an auction in  New York .  Following is a list of global wine sales scheduled for the
rest of this year. Dates may be subject to revision, and links
are to auction house sale catalogs and websites.  
